@prefix ns:     <ns#> .
@prefix def:    <ns/default#> .
@prefix rdf:        <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> .
@prefix xsd:        <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> .
@prefix dct:        <http://purl.org/dc/terms/> .
@prefix sioc:        <http://rdfs.org/sioc/ns#> .

    <command-line-interface> a def:Item ;
        dct:title "Command line interface" ;
        dct:description "Learn to use CLI to execute most of the common tasks that can be performed in the UI" ;
        sioc:content """<div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
    <p class="lead">Learn to use CLI to execute most of the common tasks that can be performed in the UI</p>
    <p>LinkedDataHub CLI wraps the <a href="http-api">HTTP API</a> into a set of shell scripts with convenient parameters. The scripts can be used for testing, automation,
        scheduled execution and such. It is usually much quicker to perform actions using CLI rather than the <a href="user-interface">user interface</a>, as well as easier to
        reproduce.</p>
    <p>Some scripts correspond to a single <a href="#atomic">atomic</a> request to LinkedDataHub. Others combine others into <a href="#tasks">tasks</a> with multiple
        interdependent requests.</p>
    <p>If you use <a href="https://dydra.com">Dydra</a> as the triplestore, you may use the Dydra-specific scripts (they accept a repository URI instead of SPARQL endpoint and graph store URIs). Otherwise, use the generic scripts.</p>
    <p><dfn>Installation</dfn> here is meant here in terms of installing (importing) the respective <a href="dataset-structure">default dataset(s)</a> into both end-user and admin
        application services. If you do not wish to install the end-user dataset as part of the task, you need to install the admin dataset separately.</p>
    <div>
        <h2 id="atomic">Atomic</h2>
        <p>Atomic commands are focused on performing a single request, such as creating a document or an application. Currently supported:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Create document</li>
            <li>Create container</li>
            <li>Apps
                <ul>
                    <li>Create context</li>
                    <li>Create end-user</li>
                    <li>Create admin</li>
                    <li>Create service</li>
                    <li>Install dataset</li>
                    <li>Dydra-specific
                        <ul>
                            <li>Create service</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>Admin
                <ul>
                    <li>Clear ontology</li>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Model
                            <ul>
                                <li>Create class</li>
                                <li>Create <code>CONSTRUCT</code> query</li>
                                <li>Create property constraint</li>
                                <li>Create restriction</li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>
                        <li>Sitemap
                            <ul>
                                <li>Create <code>CONSTRUCT</code> query</li>
                                <li>Create <code>DESCRIBE</code> query</li>
                                <li>Create template</li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>Imports
                <ul>
                    <li>Create file</li>
                    <li>Create query</li>
                    <li>Create CSV import</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
        </ul>
        <p>Usage example:</p>
        <pre>./create-file https://linkeddatahub.com/my-context/my-dataspace/ \\
-f linkeddatahub.pem \\
-p CertPassword \\
--title "Friends" \\
--file-slug 646af756-a49f-40da-a25e-ea8d81f6d306 \\
--file friends.csv \\
--file-content-type text/csv</pre>
    </div>
    <div>
        <h2 id="tasks">Tasks</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Apps
                <ul>
                    <li>Create context</li>
                    <li>Create dataspace</li>
                    <li>Install context</li>
                    <li>Install dataspace</li>
                    <li>Dydra-specific
                        <ul>
                            <li>Create context</li>
                            <li>Create dataspace</li>
                            <li>Install context</li>
                            <li>Install dataspace</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>Imports
                <ul>
                    <li>Import CSV data</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
        </ul>
        <p>Usage example:</p>
        <pre>./create-dataspace.sh \\
-b https://linkeddatahub.com/my-context/ \\
-f linkeddatahub.pem \\
-p CertPassword \\
--title "My dataspace" \\
--description "Dataspace for my data" \\
--slug my-dataspace \\
--app-base https://linkeddatahub.com/my-context/my-dataspace/ \\
--admin-endpoint http://localhost:3030/admin/sparql \\
--admin-graph-store http://localhost:3030/admin/data \\
--admin-service-user AdminServiceUser \\
--admin-service-password AdminServicePassword \\
--end-user-endpoint http://localhost:3030/end-user/sparql \\
--end-user-graph-store http://localhost:3030/end-user/data \\
--end-user-service-user EndUserServiceUser \\
--end-user-service-password EndUserServicePassword</pre>
    </div>
    <p class="lead">Find the <a href="https://github.com/AtomGraph/LinkedDataHub">CLI scripts on GitHub</a>.</p>
</div>"""^^rdf:XMLLiteral .
